title: Prenatal care in Guatemala
description:
Description
Data on the prenatal care received by mothers in Guatemala.
reference:
These data are available at
http://data.princeton.edu/multilevel/guPrenat.dat.  Multiple
indicator columns in the original data table have been collapsed to
factors for this data frame.

parameters.momEd: a factor describing the mother's level of eduation.
parameters.indig:
a factor indicating if the mother is Ladino, or
indigenous not speaking Spanish, or indigenous speaking Spanish.
parameters.childAge:
an ordered factor of the child's age at the time of
the survey.
parameters.TV:
a factor indicating if there is a TV in the house and, if
so, the frequency with which it is used.
parameters.husEmpl: a factor describing the husband's employment status.
parameters.ssDist: distance from the community to the nearest clinic.
parameters.prenat:
a factor indicating if traditional or modern prenatal
care was provided for the birth.
parameters.motherAge:
a factor indicating if the mother was older or
younger.  The cut-off age is 25 years.
parameters.mom: a factor identifying the mother or family
parameters.husEd: a factor describing the husband's level of education.
parameters.birthOrd: an ordered factor for the birth's order within the family.
parameters.pcInd81:
the percentage of indigenous population in the
community at the 1981 census.
parameters.toilet:
a factor indicating if there is a modern toilet in the
house.

format: A data frame with 2449 observations on the following 15 variables.
